<TITLE> Blast hits foreign military convoy outside Kabul </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KABUL, Sun Aug 3,(bdnews24.com/Reuters) - An explosion struck a foreign military convoy outside the Afghan capital on Sunday, a NATO spokesman said. The spokesman did not give any details of casualties in the blast in Bagrami district on the eastern outskirts of Kabul. Resurgent Taliban militants have stepped up their campaign against the government and foreign forces in Afghanistan this year, mostly relying on suicide attacks and roadside bomb blasts
